How infinite loop is declared in java?
Answer:
 use of for(;;){//your code} in the code.
 
 Example:
 
 package com.interview;
public class Sample {
     public static void main(String[] args) {
	    for (int i = 0; i <=10; i++) {
	    	System.out.println(i);
		}	
	}   
}
 

 use of while(true){//your code} in the code
 
 Example:
 
 package com.interview;


public class Sample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
    int i=0;
	while (i<=10) {
		  System.out.println(i);
    i++;
	}
	}   
}
